  "@type": "Capability",
  "critical": false,
  "description": "Extraction of edible and industrial lipids from plant seeds, fruit pulp, and animal tissues. Progression from simple pressing (40-60% yield) to expeller pressing (70-80%) to solvent extraction (95%+). Rendered animal fats (tallow, lard) serve as cooking fat, soap feedstock, and candle fuel. Industrial oils (linseed, tung) become paints and varnishes.",
  "early_win": true,
  "early_win_note": "Rendering animal fat requires only fire and containers — achievable from Year 0; vegetable oil pressing enables frying and calorie density increase",
